  ${
    $d f k m x z F $.  $d f k m n z ph $.  $d f k m x z R $.  $d f k m x z X $.
    $d x y z A $.  $d k m n S $.
    supcvg.1 $e |- X e. _V $.
    supcvg.2 $e |- S = sup ( A , RR , < ) $.
    supcvg.3 $e |- R = ( n e. NN |-> ( S - ( 1 / n ) ) ) $.
    supcvg.4 $e |- ( ph -> X =/= (/) ) $.
    supcvg.5 $e |- ( ph -> F : X -onto-> A ) $.
    supcvg.6 $e |- ( ph -> A C_ RR ) $.
    supcvg.7 $e |- ( ph -> E. x e. RR A. y e. A y <_ x ) $.
    $( Extract a sequence ` f ` in ` X ` such that the image of the points in
       the bounded set ` A ` converges to the supremum ` S ` of the set.
       Similar to Equation 4 of [Kreyszig] p. 144.  (Contributed by Mario
       Carneiro, 15-Feb-2013.)  (The proof was shortened by Mario Carneiro,
       26-Apr-2014.) $)
    supcvg $p |- ( ph -> E. f ( f : NN --> X /\ ( F o. f ) ~~> S ) ) $=
      ( cn wcel cr vk vz vm cv wf cfv cle wbr wral wa wex ccom cli wrex clt wss
      wne w3a csup wceq wfo fof syl feq3 syl5ibcom f00 simprbi syl6 necon3d mpd
      c0 3jca adantr c1 cdiv co suprcl syl5eqel nnrecre resubcl syl2an ex fmptd
      cmin ffvelrn sylan opreq2 opreq2d oprex fvmpt adantl nnrp rpreccl ltsubrp
      crp eqbrtrd syl6breq suprlub syl12anc wi ssel2 ltle syl2anc reximdva forn
      wb crn rexeqdv wfn breq2 rexrn bitr3d mpbid ralrimiva nnenom fveq2 breq2d
      ffn axcc4 cvv nnuz cz 1z a1i simpll cc0 csn cxp cmpt cc cuz eqimss2i nnex
      recnd climconst2 sylancl 0z mptex eqeltri eqeltrd ax-1cn divcnv fvconst2g
      eqid opreq12d eqtr4d climsub subid1 breqtrd fex vex coexg fss fco breq12d
      fveq2d rcla4cva adantll wfun simplll simpllr simpr fvco3 syl3anc breqtrrd
      ffun simplr syldan suprub syl6breqr climsqueeze imdistanda eximdv ) ARJGU
